text:
Warehouse Ave., (across front of view, not constructed), north side, at Bay 19th Street, showing the H. Henjes Inc. coal pockets on the east side of Bay 19th Street, between Warehouse Ave. (foreground) and Cropsey Ave. (background). At the left is a cupola topped building on the west side of Bay 19th Street, used as a summer home for children aided by the New York Children Aid Society.

April 27, 1935.

P. L. Sperr.
